net.sf.beezle.mork.compiler

Class GenericCompiler

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.sf.beezle.mork.compiler.CustomCompiler
      • net.sf.beezle.mork.compiler.GenericCompiler
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Bytecodes

    public class GenericCompiler
extends CustomCompiler
implements Bytecodes
    Compiling an object compiles it fields. The reverse process creates objects from fields. This is like serializing into a class file instead of an ObjectOutputStream. Instantiate the resulting class to "deserialize" an "bytecode"-serialized object.
